I&#x27;d have to agree, that would fit my programming style, however it&#x27;s not unreasonable for a beginner to think of slices and interfaces as basically &quot;A pointer with some additional info&quot;. So if you have two data-structures that have a slice of the same data, you may conceptualize that as two data-structures <i>pointing</i> to the same data. It&#x27;s wrong, but it&#x27;s also not far off.<p>I do think it&#x27;s a little surprising that this doesn&#x27;t work:<p><pre><code>  func append6(is []int){
    append(is, 6);
  }
</code></pre>
even though it appears to with basic testing.
